snippet.textDisplay:
heres some written instructions just in case anyone else wants them as well! ingredients list is in the description but ill copy it here as well


a wok
aluminum foil
spice grinder
a bowl
1/2 cup popcorn kernels
1/2 tsp theater salt (salt ground to a powder in a spice grinder. as fine as powdered sugar)
2-3 tbsp lao gan ma spicy chili crisp
3 tbsp vegetable oil or other neutral oil
optional, to taste: gochugaru, ground into a fine powder


put popcorn kernels into wok alongside theater salt.
take the lao gan ma and squeeze out the oil into the wok. put the remaining chilis in the bowl.
add vegetable oil
mix the oil with everything in the wok to ensure the salt is dissolved
cover the top of the wok with tinfoil. puncture some steam holes into the top
cook onto high heat and wait for kernels to pop. once they do, begin shifting wok over heat to ensure everything gets popped
stop the heat once you hear about 2-5 seconds between pops
put the wok back onto the heat, allowing any remaining kernels to pop, then stop
take off a bit of the tinfoil. add in the remaining lao gan ma from the bowl
optional: if you prefer a bit more spice you can add gochugaru as well
put the tinfoil back on
shake wok until all the pepcorn is coated
put it in a bowl and enjoy it!
